---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---


<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Rhumb's privacy policy. What we collect, what we don't, and how we handle your data."
  canonical="/privacy"
>
  <div class="bg-navy min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-14 pb-24">
      <header class="mb-12">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono font-semibold text-amber uppercase tracking-widest">
          Legal
        </span>
        <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl text-slate-100 leading-tight tracking-tight mt-4 mb-4">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-mono">
          Last updated: March 20, 2026
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Overview
          </h2>
          <p>
            Rhumb (operated by Supertrained Inc.) is a developer tool that
            scores APIs for AI agent compatibility and provides managed
            capability execution. We are committed to
            transparency about what we collect and why.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong class="text-slate-200">
              The short version: we collect what we need to operate the service,
              we don&#39;t sell any of it, and we don&#39;t track you across sites.
            </strong>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            What we collect
          </h2>

          <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-base text-slate-200 mt-6 mb-2">
            Account data (if you sign up)
          </h3>
          <p>
            When you create an account via GitHub or Google OAuth, we receive and store:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-2">
            <li>&bull; Your display name and email address (from your OAuth provider)</li>
            <li>&bull; Your OAuth provider identifier (GitHub user ID or Google sub)</li>
            <li>&bull; An API key we generate for your account</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We do <strong class="text-slate-200">not</strong> receive or store your
            OAuth provider password. We use the standard OAuth 2.0 authorization code
            flow with CSRF protection.
          </p>

          <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-base text-slate-200 mt-6 mb-2">
            Session data
          </h3>
          <p>
            When you sign in, we set a <code class="text-amber/80 bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">rhumb_session</code>{" "}
            cookie containing a signed JWT token. This cookie is:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-2">
            <li>&bull; HttpOnly (not accessible to JavaScript)</li>
            <li>&bull; Secure (only transmitted over HTTPS)</li>
            <li>&bull; SameSite=Lax (not sent on cross-site requests)</li>
            <li>&bull; Valid for 7 days</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-base text-slate-200 mt-6 mb-2">
            API and execution data
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-2">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">API query logs:</strong>{" "}
              Search terms, capability execution requests, and timestamps.
              Authenticated requests are associated with your API key.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Execution records:</strong>{" "}
              When you use managed capability execution, we log the capability called,
              provider used, latency, cost, and success/failure status. We do{" "}
              <strong class="text-slate-200">not</strong> log the contents of your
              request bodies or upstream responses.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Error logs:</strong>{" "}
              Server error logs may contain request metadata (URL, HTTP method, status code)
              for debugging. These are retained for 30 days.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-base text-slate-200 mt-6 mb-2">
            Payment data
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-2">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Stripe:</strong>{" "}
              Payment processing is handled by Stripe. We store your Stripe customer ID
              and transaction records (amounts, dates). We do{" "}
              <strong class="text-slate-200">not</strong> store your credit card number
              or payment method details — those are held by Stripe.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">x402/USDC:</strong>{" "}
              For on-chain payments, we record the transaction hash and wallet address
              used for payment verification. Blockchain transactions are inherently public.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-base text-slate-200 mt-6 mb-2">
            Web analytics
          </h3>
          <p>
            We use Google Analytics 4 and Microsoft Clarity for
            anonymized usage analytics on <code class="text-amber/80 bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">rhumb.dev</code>.
            These tools collect standard web metrics (page views, session duration, device type).
            Both are configured with IP anonymization enabled.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            What we do NOT collect
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>&bull; We do not store your OAuth provider password</li>
            <li>&bull; We do not store credit card numbers (Stripe handles payment details)</li>
            <li>&bull; We do not log upstream API request/response bodies from managed executions</li>
            <li>&bull; We do not track you across other websites</li>
            <li>
              &bull; We do not build advertising profiles or sell data to third
              parties
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; We do not use your API queries or execution data to train machine learning
              models
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Managed credentials
          </h2>
          <p>
            When you use Rhumb-managed capability execution, we hold API credentials
            for upstream services on your behalf. These credentials:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>&bull; Are stored in encrypted secret management infrastructure</li>
            <li>&bull; Are never exposed in API responses, logs, or error messages</li>
            <li>&bull; Are used only to execute the specific capability you request</li>
            <li>&bull; Are shared across users of managed capabilities (they are Rhumb&#39;s
              credentials, not per-user credentials)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            If you use <strong class="text-slate-200">bring-your-own-key (BYOK)</strong>{" "}
            mode, your credentials are passed through to the upstream service in the same
            request and are <strong class="text-slate-200">not stored</strong> by Rhumb.
            If you use <strong class="text-slate-200">Agent Vault</strong>, Rhumb stores an encrypted
            provider credential scoped to your agent, injects it only at call time,
            and does not share it across accounts.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            How we use your data
          </h2>
          <p>Data collected is used to:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>&bull; Authenticate your identity and manage your account</li>
            <li>&bull; Process payments and maintain billing records</li>
            <li>&bull; Execute capability requests on your behalf</li>
            <li>&bull; Enforce budget limits and rate controls</li>
            <li>&bull; Improve search relevance and service coverage</li>
            <li>&bull; Monitor API performance, uptime, and error rates</li>
            <li>
              &bull; Understand aggregate usage patterns (which capabilities are
              most used, which services are most queried)
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Third-party services
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 mt-3">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">GitHub / Google</strong>{" "}
              — OAuth identity providers.{" "}
              <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Privacy</a>{" / "}
              <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Stripe</strong>{" "}
              — payment processing.{" "}
              <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Stripe Privacy Policy</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">
                Google Analytics 4
              </strong>{" "}
              — anonymized web analytics.{" "}
              <a
                href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                Google Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">
                Microsoft Clarity
              </strong>{" "}
              — session recordings and heatmaps (anonymized).{" "}
              <a
                href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-us/privacystatement"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                Microsoft Privacy Statement
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Vercel</strong> —
              frontend hosting.{" "}
              <a
                href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                Vercel Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Railway</strong> —
              API hosting.{" "}
              <a
                href="https://railway.com/legal/privacy"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                Railway Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Supabase</strong> —
              database hosting.{" "}
              <a
                href="https://supabase.com/privacy"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                Supabase Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            When using managed capabilities, your requests are proxied through upstream
            service APIs (e.g., Stripe, GitHub, Twilio, Slack). Each upstream service
            has its own privacy policy governing data they receive through API calls.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Your rights (GDPR / CCPA)
          </h2>
          <p>You have the right to:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>
              &bull; <strong class="text-slate-200">Access</strong> —
              request a copy of all data associated with your account
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; <strong class="text-slate-200">Correction</strong> —
              request correction of inaccurate data
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; <strong class="text-slate-200">Deletion</strong> —
              request deletion of your account and associated data
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; <strong class="text-slate-200">Opt-out of analytics</strong> —
              disable web analytics by using a browser ad blocker or
              Do Not Track setting
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull;{" "}
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Data portability</strong>{" "}
              — request your data in a machine-readable format
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull;{" "}
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Non-discrimination</strong>{" "}
              — exercising these rights will not affect your service access
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            For any privacy-related requests, contact{" "}
            <a
              href="mailto:privacy@supertrained.ai"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >
              privacy@supertrained.ai
            </a>
            . We will respond within 30 days.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Data retention
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>&bull; Account data: retained while your account is active; deleted within 30 days of account deletion request</li>
            <li>&bull; API query and execution logs: retained for 90 days</li>
            <li>&bull; Error logs: retained for 30 days</li>
            <li>&bull; Billing records: retained for 7 years (tax/legal compliance)</li>
            <li>
              &bull; Web analytics: per Google Analytics and Microsoft Clarity
              default retention policies
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Children&#39;s privacy
          </h2>
          <p>
            Rhumb is a developer tool not intended for use by children under 13.
            We do not knowingly collect data from children under 13. If you believe
            a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us
            at{" "}
            <a
              href="mailto:privacy@supertrained.ai"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >privacy@supertrained.ai</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Changes to this policy
          </h2>
          <p>
            We will update this page when our data practices change. For
            significant changes, we&#39;ll note the update in our{" "}
            <a
              href="/changelog"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >
              changelog
            </a>
            .
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Contact
          </h2>
          <p>
            For privacy-related questions or requests:
            <br />
            <a
              href="mailto:privacy@supertrained.ai"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >
              privacy@supertrained.ai
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Supertrained Inc.
            <br />
            7901 4th St N STE 300
            <br />
            St Petersburg, FL 33702
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
